body: Hey @donatj, can you reproduce the issue on https://psalm.dev ?
Can't reproduce with https://psalm.dev/r/a9d5c1af5c, so there must be something about your interfaces/factory/user object that triggers this issues.

I *am* able to reproduce but when I try to copy a link I get 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/133747/90452762-8f3b8880-e0b4-11ea-9d46-d1a68da9d18b.png)


![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/133747/90452735-7c28b880-e0b4-11ea-8bba-95eb0ca1b0f8.png)
Is there an email address I could send the blob to? I'd rather not post all of this publicly.
You can send that to the address in my profile. Note that I don't have any affiliations with Vimeo or Psalm, so you'll effectively be sending that to a random stranger.
But a very reliable random stranger

Nice reproducer. You can also see the result on psalm.dev in the ajax on the console:

> Fatal error: Allowed memory size of 268435456 bytes exhausted (tried to allocate 167772160 bytes) in /var/www/vhosts/psalm.dev/httpdocs/vendor/vimeo/psalm/src/Psalm/Internal/Analyzer/Statements/Expression/Call/Method/AtomicMethodCallAnalyzer.php on line 490

Psalm build a lot of complex types internally:
https://psalm.dev/r/a1e99c7462

> INFO: Trace - 34:37 - $foo: Base&A&B&C&D&E|Base&A&B&C&E|Base&A&B&D&E|Base&A&B&E|Base&A&C&D&E|Base&A&C&E|Base&A&D&E|Base&A&E|Base&B&C&D&E|Base&B&C&E|Base&B&D&E|Base&B&E|Base&C&D&E|Base&C&E|Base&D&E|Base&E
Ok, this should be fairly simple to work around
